g.title: myTitle
g.text: @: -1EST per AR with talisman, +4 damage with trident
$: -1ESK with loth talisman, +5 damage with trident
Current skill is not capped by initial skill.
You can only eat when instructed.
rage potion: +4SK on next battle, but must fight til the death
runic axe: +2ISK, but must decide to fight if possible, and never escape
trident: +2SK, +2 damage vs human, +4 damage vs non-human
The runic axe's description is inconsistent. Choosing fight every time will get you killed before you reach the dungeons.
That makes no sense with the options given in those sections of the book, so I assume it only applies when it is explicitly stated.
Book is inconsistent on whether to add/subtract skill vs initial skill with weapons, so just assume they all modify attack strength.
I have duplicated the death nodes 348 and 157, as they occur in unrelated parts of the path.
You want to get the trident if possible, which means the luck roll at the beginning is very important.
You want the loth talisman and green globe to skip the final battle.
Take rage potion in case you have to fight Xakhaz.
The weapons in the armory is not worth the trouble unless you skill 10 or higher, and don't have the trident head.
Take ordeal if your combined willpower and stamina is at least 28 for 50% chance to gain stats.
While you can get a free luck point from the riverside, you don't need it as you can get one after getting arrested.

a.xlink:title: stay in after dark, find old huw at ruined temple
find talisman of loth, use side entrance right of main gate
buy trident head at merchant's quarter, avoid riverside
never use loth talisman in front of mirror
